               <head>Novellae on the Babylonian Talmud </head>
               
               
               
               <msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/n80020282" rend="visible">
                  
                  
                  
                  <summary>Novellae on the Babylonian Talmud</summary>
                  
                  
                  
                  <textLang mainLang="he">Hebrew</textLang>
                  
                  
                  
                  <msItem rend="visible">
                     
                     
                     
                     <locus from="1r" to="103r"/>
                     
                     
                     
                     <title xml:lang="he">חדושים על התלמוד</title>
                     
                     
                     
                     <title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Ḥidushim ʽal ha-Talmud</title>
                     
                     
                     
                     <note>
                        
                        
                        
                        <note>Collected by <persName>Meir Braḥ me-Glogau</persName>.</note>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>Title given on the title page: ליקוטים חדשים גם ישנים נחלק לארבעה חלקים</p>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>On the title page: "אשר אספתי ולקטתי ולרוב שמעתי אותם מפי רב ... צבי אב"ד דק"ק גלוגא ומפי בנו ... יהודא ליבש אב"ד דק"ק קאמערנא ... אני הצעיר שבתלמידיהם <persName>מאיר ברא"ח גלוגא</persName>"</p>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>Title in the manuscript: "What I collected and compiled and mostly heard from the mouth of the Rabbi […] Tzvi chief of the court of the holy community of <placeName>Glogau</placeName>, and from the mouth of his son.. Yehudah Libesh chief of the court of the holy community of Komarno [..] I am the youngest among their desciples - Me'ir of Glogau".</p>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>Includes also novellae by others. Among them are Rabbi Yosef chief of the court of the community of <placeName>Poznan</placeName> (פוזנא) (48b), and David Sender the scribe of the court of the community of Kepno (קעמפנא).</p>
                     
                     
                     
                     </note>
                  
                  
                  
                  </msItem>
               
               
               
